# Chadpress agent rules

Chadpress is a Next.js + WordPress monorepo. WordPress supplies content through WPGraphQL Content Blocks; `packages/ui` supplies the block contracts and pure React renderers shared by Gutenberg and the frontend.

Before changing blocks, read `packages/ui/blocks/README.md`.

## Non-negotiables

1. Author only custom `chadpress/*` blocks. Never add `core/*` shadow declarations or depend on Core Group, Columns, or other Core blocks. Custom layout blocks are the intended architecture.
2. Treat each `block.json` as the complete contract: attributes, supports, capabilities, semantic styles, controls, custom-editor policy, variations, and `example.attributes`.
3. Render the same framework-agnostic React component in WordPress and Next.js. No WordPress or Next.js imports in `packages/ui` block components.
4. Declare every editable string per attribute with `richText: true`, `tagName`, and `placeholder`. Components render the corresponding named slot in the editor and persisted HTML on the frontend. Support multiple slots.
5. Reuse the closed `align` and `spacing` capabilities. Do not duplicate their attributes, controls, or class logic.
6. Controls must use only the implemented closed vocabulary: `select`, `toggle`, `text`, `alignment`, `headingLevel`, and `link`. Every control binds a real explicit or capability-provided attribute and covers all supported options.
7. Keep WordPress restricted to the declaration-derived `chadpress/*` allowlist. Do not weaken the allowlist to accommodate an undeclared block.
8. Keep GraphQL flat: request `editorBlocks(flat: true)` with `clientId` / `parentClientId`, rebuild the tree in the web app, and render through `blockRegistry`. Do not add recursive depth fragments or `renderedHtml` fallbacks.
9. Generated registry and barrel files come from the filesystem scan. Do not hand-edit them or maintain parallel block lists.

## Block workflow

Use the canonical anatomy:

```text
packages/ui/blocks/<slug>/
  block.json
  <Name>Block.tsx
  <slug>-variants.ts   # optional
  types.ts
  index.ts
```

From `packages/ui`, use:

```sh
node scripts/create-block.mjs <slug> "<Title>"
pnpm generate:registry
pnpm validate:contracts
```

For every new or changed block, follow: **contract → scaffold → implement → validate → `/dev/blocks` gallery screenshot**. Define representative `example.attributes`, add `example.innerBlocks` for containers, run generation and validation, then visually inspect the real renderer in the gallery. Do not bypass failures or create separate fixture data.

Do not add configurable arbitrary Tailwind branches in components. Map contract values to semantic CVA variants or shared capability classes. Components own complete DOM anatomy, including rich-text slot placement and child content.
